1305	    /// `lua_close(L)` destroys a Lua state. In Rust the state's resources are
1306	    /// released by `Drop` when the owning value goes out of scope, so the
1307	    /// in-place `&mut self` form is a no-op. The consuming free function
1308	    /// `lua_vm::state::close(state)` is reserved for the top-level shutdown
1309	    /// path in `lua-cli`.
